eriDNXLinkPMStatsMIB.name: eriDNXLinkPMStatsMIB
eriDNXLinkPMStatsMIB.contactinfo: Customer Service Postal: Eastern Research, Inc. 225 Executive Drive Moorestown, NJ 08057 Phone: +1-800-337-4374 Email: support@erinc.com
eriDNXLinkPMStatsMIB.description: The ERI Enterprise MIB Module for the DNX DSx1 Performance Monitoring.

dsx1EsfCurrTable.name: dsx1EsfCurrTable
dsx1EsfCurrTable.description: This is the DS1/E1 ESF Current Statistics table which consists of an entry for each DS1 link in the system that is configured for T1 ESF lines. This table provides the counters for the current 15 minute time interval.

dsx1EsfCurrEntry.name: dsx1EsfCurrEntry
dsx1EsfCurrEntry.description: The conceptual row of the DS1/E1 ESF Statistics table. A row in this table cannot be added, deleted, or modified directly. Rows may be removed or added by configuring the DS1 line type via the appropriate Device Provisioning table.

dsx1EsfCurrLinkAddr.name: dsx1EsfCurrLinkAddr
dsx1EsfCurrLinkAddr.description: This number uniquely identifies an DS1/E1 link resource. This number will be used throughout the system to identify a unique link. The format is represented using an IP address syntax (4 byte string). Note that the maximum valid link number will vary depending on the specified carrier and framing options. For example, an octal T1/E1 device has 8 DS1 links however the DS3 has 28 DS1 links. The 1st byte is reserved for future Nest Number use The 2nd byte represents the Slot Number (1-11) The 3rd byte represents the Link Number (1-84) The 4th byte is reserved for future use

dsx1EsfCurrResrcId.name: dsx1EsfCurrResrcId
dsx1EsfCurrResrcId.description: Uniquely identifies a link in the system. This number is provided as key to allow the manager to map this entry to a corresponding Resource Table entry.

dsx1EsfCurrESs.name: dsx1EsfCurrESs
dsx1EsfCurrESs.description: This is the number of errored seconds that have occurred on the link during the current interval. This is not incremented during an Unavailable Second. For ESF links an Errored Second is a second with the occurrence of a Loss of Frame or a CRC6 error in a one-second period.

dsx1EsfCurrUASs.name: dsx1EsfCurrUASs
dsx1EsfCurrUASs.description: This is the number of failed seconds (UAS) that have occurred on the link during the current interval. Unavailable Seconds (UAS) are calculated by counting the number of seconds that the interface is unavailable. Each second period during the occurrence of a Failed Signal State (ten consecutive SES) is known as a failed/unavailable second.

dsx1EsfCurrSESs.name: dsx1EsfCurrSESs
dsx1EsfCurrSESs.description: This is the number of severely errored seconds that have occurred on the link during the current interval. Controlled slips are not included in this parameter. This is not incremented during an Unavailable Second. A Severely Errored Second for ESF signals is a second period with 320 or more CRC6 errors.

dsx1EsfCurrBESs.name: dsx1EsfCurrBESs
dsx1EsfCurrBESs.description: This is the number of bursty errored seconds that have occurred on the T1 link during the current interval. This is not incremented during an Unavailable Second and applies to ESF signals only. A Bursty Errored Second is a second period with more than one but less than 320 CRC6 errors.

dsx1EsfCurrLOFs.name: dsx1EsfCurrLOFs
dsx1EsfCurrLOFs.description: This is the number of loss of frames that have occurred on the link during the current interval. A loss of frame occurs when either network equipment or the DTE senses errors in the framing pattern. Depending upon the equipment, this occurs when any 2 of 4, 2 of 5, or 3 of 5 consecutive terminal framing bits received contain bit errors in the framing pattern.

dsx1EsfCurrSeconds.name: dsx1EsfCurrSeconds
dsx1EsfCurrSeconds.description: The total number of seconds in the current interval.

dsx1EsfCurrIntervals.name: dsx1EsfCurrIntervals
dsx1EsfCurrIntervals.description: The total number of valid 15 minute intervals counted since the link has been up and running.

dsx1EsfCurrStatus.name: dsx1EsfCurrStatus
dsx1EsfCurrStatus.description: This defines the status of the DS1/E1 link using an 8 character code which can contain numbers or letters. The codes are interpreted as follows: character #1 - 'F' or zero where 'F' indicates Failed Signal Status (FSS) if 'U' or 'L' are present. character #2 - 'U' or zero where 'U' indicates an unavailable signal state. character #3 through #6 are always zero. character #7 - 'L' or zero where 'L' indicates that the T1 line is in loop. character #8 - always zero.

dsx1Esf24HrTable.name: dsx1Esf24HrTable
dsx1Esf24HrTable.description: This is the DS1/E1 24 Hour ESF Statistics table which consists of an entry for each DS1/E1 link in the system that is configured for T1 ESF lines. This table provides the total counters accumulated for last 24 hour period.

dsx1Esf24HrEntry.name: dsx1Esf24HrEntry
dsx1Esf24HrEntry.description: The conceptual row of the DS1/E1 24 Hour ESF Statistics table. A row in this table cannot be added, deleted, or modified directly. Rows may be removed or added by configuring the DS1 line type via the appropriate Device Provisioning table.

dsx1Esf24HrLinkAddr.name: dsx1Esf24HrLinkAddr
dsx1Esf24HrLinkAddr.description: This number uniquely identifies an DS1/E1 link resource. This number will be used throughout the system to identify a unique link. The format is represented using an IP address syntax (4 byte string). Note that the maximum valid link number will vary depending on the specified carrier and framing options. For example, an octal T1/E1 device has 8 DS1 links but the DS3 has 28 DS1 links. The 1st byte is reserved for future Nest Number use The 2nd byte represents the Slot Number (1-11) The 3rd byte represents the Link Number (1-84) The 4th byte is reserved for future use

dsx1Esf24HrResrcId.name: dsx1Esf24HrResrcId
dsx1Esf24HrResrcId.description: Uniquely identifies a link in the system. This number is provided as key to allow the manager to map this entry to a corresponding Resource Table entry.

dsx1Esf24HrESs.name: dsx1Esf24HrESs
dsx1Esf24HrESs.description: This is the number of errored seconds that have occurred on the link during the past 24 hours.

dsx1Esf24HrUASs.name: dsx1Esf24HrUASs
dsx1Esf24HrUASs.description: This is the number of Unavailable Seconds (UAS) that have occurred on the T1 link during the past 24 hours.

dsx1Esf24HrSESs.name: dsx1Esf24HrSESs
dsx1Esf24HrSESs.description: This is the number of severely errored seconds that have occurred on the T1 link during the past 24 hours.

dsx1Esf24HrBESs.name: dsx1Esf24HrBESs
dsx1Esf24HrBESs.description: This is the number of bursty errored seconds that have occurred on the T1 link during the past 24 hours.

dsx1Esf24HrLOFs.name: dsx1Esf24HrLOFs
dsx1Esf24HrLOFs.description: This is the number of loss of frames that have occurred on the T1 link during the past 24 hours.

dsx1Esf96RegTable.name: dsx1Esf96RegTable
dsx1Esf96RegTable.description: This table is the ESF 96 Registers Table. It displays the 96 15 minute performance registers for each link on a card

dsx1Esf96RegEntry.name: dsx1Esf96RegEntry
dsx1Esf96RegEntry.description: The conceptual row of the DS1/E1 ESF 96 Registers table. A row in this table cannot be added, deleted, or modified directly. Rows may be removed or added by configuring the DS1 line type via the appropriate Device Provisioning table.

dsx1Esf96RegLinkAddr.name: dsx1Esf96RegLinkAddr
dsx1Esf96RegLinkAddr.description: Uniquely identifies a link in the system. This number is provided as key to allow the manager to map this entry to a corresponding Resource Table entry.

dsx1Esf96RegInterval.name: dsx1Esf96RegInterval
dsx1Esf96RegInterval.description: Specifies the interval Number On a particular link

dsx1Esf96RegESs.name: dsx1Esf96RegESs
dsx1Esf96RegESs.description: The number of Errored Seconds for a particular interval on a particular link

dsx1Esf96RegUASs.name: dsx1Esf96RegUASs
dsx1Esf96RegUASs.description: The number of Unavailable Seconds for a particular interval on a particular link

dsx1Esf96RegSESs.name: dsx1Esf96RegSESs
dsx1Esf96RegSESs.description: The number of Severely Errored Seconds for a particular interval on a particular link

dsx1Esf96RegBESs.name: dsx1Esf96RegBESs
dsx1Esf96RegBESs.description: The number of Bursty Errored Seconds for a particular interval on a particular link

dsx1G826Table.name: dsx1G826Table
dsx1G826Table.description: This is the DS1/E1 G.826 Statistics table which consists of an entry for each DS1/E1 link in the system. This table provides the total counters accumulated since the link has been up or since the last time the counts were cleared. The counters are calculated in accordance with the ITU-T G.826 Error performance parameters, November 1993.

dsx1G826Entry.name: dsx1G826Entry
dsx1G826Entry.description: The conceptual row of the DS1/E1 G.826 Statistics table. A row in this table cannot be added or deleted directly but the counter time period can be reset to zero. Rows may be removed or added by configuring the DS1/E1 line type via the appropriate Device Provisioning tables.

dsx1G826LinkAddr.name: dsx1G826LinkAddr
dsx1G826LinkAddr.description: This number uniquely identifies an DS1/E1 link resource. This number will be used throughout the system to identify a unique link. The format is represented using an IP address syntax (4 byte string). Note that the maximum valid link number will vary depending on the specified carrier and framing options. For example, an octal T1/E1 device has 8 DS1 links but the DS3 has 28 DS1 links. The 1st byte is reserved for future Nest Number use The 2nd byte represents the Slot Number (1-11) The 3rd byte represents the Link Number (1-84) The 4th byte is reserved for future use

dsx1G826ResrcId.name: dsx1G826ResrcId
dsx1G826ResrcId.description: Uniquely identifies a link in the system. This number is provided as key to allow the manager to map this entry to a corresponding Resource Table entry.

dsx1G826TotalTime.name: dsx1G826TotalTime
dsx1G826TotalTime.description: This the total number of seconds the G.826 data has been collected. Resetting this to zero will clear the counters for specific link.

dsx1G826ESs.name: dsx1G826ESs
dsx1G826ESs.description: This is the total number of errored seconds that have occurred since the link has been up or since the G.826 counters have been reset. An Errored Second for G.826 is a one second period with one or more errored blocks or at least one defect.

dsx1G826ErrFSs.name: dsx1G826ErrFSs
dsx1G826ErrFSs.description: This is the total number of error free seconds since the link has been up or since the G.826 counters have been reset.

dsx1G826SESs.name: dsx1G826SESs
dsx1G826SESs.description: This is the total number of severely errored seconds that have occurred since the link has been up or since the G.826 counters have been reset. A Severely Errored Second for G.826 is a one second period that contains 30% or more errored blocks OR at least one defect. This is a subset of ES.

dsx1G826ConsecSESs.name: dsx1G826ConsecSESs
dsx1G826ConsecSESs.description: This is the total number of continuous occurrences of SES, in a one second intervals, since the link has been up or since the G.826 counters have been reset.

dsx1G826ConsecErrFSs.name: dsx1G826ConsecErrFSs
dsx1G826ConsecErrFSs.description: This is the total number of consecutive seconds one second period intervals that did not have defects or errors since the link has been up or since the G.826 counters have been reset.

dsx1G826BGErrBlocks.name: dsx1G826BGErrBlocks
dsx1G826BGErrBlocks.description: This is the total number of background errored blocks that have occurred since the link has been up or since the G.826 counters have been reset. A Background Block Error for G.826 is an errored block not occurring as part of an SES.

dsx1G826ESRatio.name: dsx1G826ESRatio
dsx1G826ESRatio.description: This is the ratio of ES to total seconds in available time during a fixed measurement interval rounded to 2 decimals.

dsx1G826SESRatio.name: dsx1G826SESRatio
dsx1G826SESRatio.description: This is the ratio of SES to total seconds in available time during a fixed measurement interval rounded to 2 decimals.

dsx1G826BgBERRatio.name: dsx1G826BgBERRatio
dsx1G826BgBERRatio.description: This is the ratio of background block errors to total blocks in available time during a fixed measurement interval rounded to 2 decimals. This total block count excludes all blocks during SES.

dsx1G826UASs.name: dsx1G826UASs
dsx1G826UASs.description: This is the total number of Unavailable Seconds (UAS) that have occurred since the link has been up or since the G.826 counters have been reset.
